The Lakers entered the game missing their two best players, LeBron James and Anthony Davis, but they overcame that with energetic play, strong perimeter shooting and a lockdown defenceIn Salt Lake City, Donovan Mitchell scored 42 points and the Utah Jazz won their 24th consecutive game at home with a 128-112 victory over the Sacramento KingsDevin Booker's 27 points, double-doubles from both Chris Paul and Deandre Ayton, helped the Phoenix Suns to a dominating 134-106 victory over the Washington Wizards